2007-08-13 04:31  tfonrouge

	* ChangeLog:

2007-08-13 04:30  tfonrouge

	* ChangeLog, INSTALL, config/Makefile.run: [SOLVED] hblnk under
	  MinGW fails.
	  * Linking is different in gcc & g++, hblnk is forcing (via a
	  HB_COMPILER="mingw32" in the hblnk script) linking with gcc, when
	  compiling using g++ the linking process is ok and the binary
	  executable is builded ok.
	  Currently using gcc/g++ version: 3.4.2 (mingw-special)
	  TODO: Check with Harbour developers if the hblnk script can be
	  changed to no hardcode the HB_COMPILER="mingw32" env var. Anyway
	  I think we can override this by issuing a parameter when linking
	  via gcc.

